  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nWhen the file in `build-info/` is too big (in our case ~263M) hardhat node crashes after a few seconds without output. Even with a heap size of 12GB [1]. This actually happened during `hardhat test`, **without any logs indicating this is a hardhat node's issue**.\r\n\r\nDeleting the file inside `build-info/` allows `npx hardhat node` to run.\r\n\r\nAnother project has a `build-info` file around 100MB and hardhat node works, but it has a **notable delay** (~5s) compared with launching after deleting the file.\r\n\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n  <summary>[1] OOM console output</summary>\r\n  \r\n\r\n```\r\n$ NODE_OPTIONS=\"--max-old-space-size=12000\" npx hardhat node\r\n\r\n<--- Last few GCs --->\r\n\r\n[432788:0x54c4e60]    62007 ms: Mark-sweep 11816.8 (12032.6) -> 11811.5 (12032.6) MB, 3509.3 / 0.0 ms  (average mu = 0.331, current mu = 0.083) allocation failure scavenge might not succeed\r\n[432788:0x54c4e60]    68234 ms: Mark-sweep 11828.6 (12032.9) -> 11828.5 (12060.4) MB, 6221.0 / 0.0 ms  (average mu = 0.181, current mu = 0.001) allocation failure scavenge might not succeed\r\n\r\n\r\n<--- JS stacktrace --->\r\n\r\nFATAL ERROR: Reached heap limit Allocation failed - JavaScript heap out of memory\r\n 1: 0xb0a860 node::Abort() [node]\r\n 2: 0xa1c193 node::FatalError(char const*, char const*) [node]\r\n 3: 0xcf9a6e v8::Utils::ReportOOMFailure(v8::internal::Isolate*, char const*, bool) [node]\r\n 4: 0xcf9de7 v8::internal::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(v8::internal::Isolate*, char const*, bool) [node]\r\n 5: 0xeb1685  [node]\r\n 6: 0xec134d v8::internal::Heap::CollectGarbage(v8::internal::AllocationSpace, v8::internal::GarbageCollectionReason, v8::GCCallbackFlags) [node]\r\n 7: 0xec404e v8::internal::Heap::AllocateRawWithRetryOrFailSlowPath(int, v8::internal::AllocationType, v8::internal::AllocationOrigin, v8::internal::AllocationAlignment) [node]\r\n 8: 0xe8558a v8::internal::Factory::NewFillerObject(int, bool, v8::internal::AllocationType, v8::internal::AllocationOrigin) [node]\r\n 9: 0x11fe2d6 v8::internal::Runtime_AllocateInYoungGeneration(int, unsigned long*, v8::internal::Isolate*) [node]\r\n10: 0x15f2d39  [node]\r\nAborted (core dumped)\r\n```\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n\r\n## Related issues\r\n\r\n- #1186\r\n- #2803\r\n\r\n## Quick-Fix questions\r\n\r\nWhat are the drawbacks of deleting `build-info/` between compilation and tests?\r\nWhy would `hardhat node` need to load that info?\r\n",
