    "body": "> What are the drawbacks of deleting `build-info/` between compilation and tests?\r\n> Why would `hardhat node` need to load that info?\r\n\r\nHardhat uses the compilation output to generate stack traces and infer the cause of reverted transactions. You can delete them and run `npx hardhat test --no-compile` and your tests should work fine, but if something fails you'll get less information.\r\n\r\nThanks for reporting this, it seems important.",
