    "body": "@fvictorio sadly no, but you can generate a contract doing something like this (tested locally with 8GB of RAM and hardhat v2.12.4):\r\n- Create new contract `A.sol` with:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-3.0\r\npragma solidity >=0.7.0 <0.9.0;\r\ncontract A {\r\n    string bigasstext = \"\r\n```\r\n> No new line at the end!\r\n\r\n\r\n- In terminal generate a lot of random text in a single line (change `count=` to adapt size):\r\n```bash\r\nrandom=$(dd if=/dev/urandom bs=1 count=100000000 | tr -dc 'a-zA-Z0-9~!@#$%^&*_-' | base64 -w 0)\r\n```\r\n> This may take a while...\r\n\r\n\r\n- Then append at the end without new lines:\r\n```bash\r\nprintf \"%s%s%s\" \"$(cat contracts/A.sol)\" \"$random\" \"\\\"; }\" > contracts/A.sol\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Compile, check size and try to run hh node:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n$ npx hardhat compile\r\nCompiled 1 Solidity file successfully\r\n\r\n$ du -h artifacts/build-info/\r\n413M\tartifacts/build-info/\r\n\r\n$ npx hardhat node\r\n\r\n<--- Last few GCs --->\r\n\r\n[32438:0x6ed9130]    33131 ms: Scavenge 2022.8 (2053.5) -> 2022.8 (2058.3) MB, 8.0 / 0.0 ms  (average mu = 0.176, current mu = 0.153) allocation failure; \r\n[32438:0x6ed9130]    33146 ms: Scavenge 2025.9 (2058.3) -> 2026.2 (2059.8) MB, 9.8 / 0.0 ms  (average mu = 0.176, current mu = 0.153) allocation failure; \r\n[32438:0x6ed9130]    33159 ms: Scavenge 2026.9 (2059.8) -> 2026.6 (2070.8) MB, 12.1 / 0.0 ms  (average mu = 0.176, current mu = 0.153) allocation failure; \r\n\r\n\r\n<--- JS stacktrace --->\r\n\r\nFATAL ERROR: Ineffective mark-compacts near heap limit Allocation failed - JavaScript heap out of memory\r\n 1: 0xb6e500 node::Abort() [node]\r\n[...]\r\n```\r\n",
